From: Shannon Nelson <shannon.nelson@intel.com>
Date: Tue, 26 Nov 2013 10:49:26 +0000
Subject: [PATCH v3 088/474] i40e: prevent null pointer exception in dump
 descriptor
Patch-mainline: v3.14-rc1
Git-commit: 29d0790ef3acd869bc392676a7623e5613ab33e8
References: bsc#909484 FATE#317397

Check that rings were allocated before trying to reference them.

Change-Id: I33151e55ab7a7a305fecdb88ccb2709ac246b7c7
Signed-off-by: Shannon Nelson <shannon.nelson@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Jesse Brandeburg <jesse.brandeburg@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Jeff Kirsher <jeffrey.t.kirsher@intel.com>
Acked-by: David Chang <dchang@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/i40e/i40e_debugfs.c |    6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/i40e/i40e_debugfs.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/i40e/i40e_debugfs.c
@@ -782,6 +782,12 @@ static void i40e_dbg_dump_desc(int cnt,
 			dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "dump desc tx <vsi_seid> <ring_id> [<desc_n>]\n");
 		return;
 	}
+	if (!vsi->tx_rings) {
+		dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
+			 "descriptor rings have not been allocated for vsi %d\n",
+			 vsi_seid);
+		return;
+	}
 	if (is_rx_ring)
 		ring = *vsi->rx_rings[ring_id];
 	else
